        tekst: 'Together with N!D we make the podcast for shared mobility in the Netherlands, with the same name. Every episode one or two interesting guests join to explain a different piece of the puzzle. The podcast is recorded in our podcast studio in The Hague. The goal: give civil servants and policymakers an accessible knowledge boost about this rapidly developing theme. We also make snippets of every episode for social media. Two birds with one stone!',
        spotify: 'https://open.spotify.com/embed/show/0UWucGAIw9miV2azC0MYvY?utm_source=generator',
        flip: false,
      },
      {
        label: 'Video',
        titel: 'Street interviews and in-depth aftermovies',
        tekst: 'We make several types of videos for N!D. With street interviews we collect the opinions of people on the street and share them with government parties and businesses. From events we make in-depth aftermovies that share the main message with an online audience afterwards. This way we hold attention, the key lessons stick, and we amplify the impact.',
        mave: [
          { src: 'https://space-10z8x.video-dns.com/8inYzSnFG7/player.html', titel: 'Shared Mobility Rocks' },
        ],
        flip: true,
      },
      {
        label: 'Webinar',
        titel: 'An interactive panel programme',
        tekst: 'The chair or presenter takes viewers through a substantive programme, optionally alternated with videos. Think of a short break with street interviews about the next substantive topic coming up. Viewers can ask live questions to the panel guests or, where needed, request additional depth.',
